[3] USA: Florida (Polk County) bat, dog
Date: Thu 3 Mar 2022
Source: WFTV
https://bit.ly/3KBFQaq


Animal Control officials have confirmed the 1st case of rabies this year [2022] in Polk County.

Officials said a bat had tested positive for the deadly virus on [3 Mar 2022].

According to the Polk County Sheriff's Office Animal Control Section, a family dog in the Lake Mirror area of Winter Haven was found with a live bat in its mouth on [1 Mar 2022].

The family contacted Animal Control which then sent the bat to a Tampa lab for testing.

Officials say the dog was current on its rabies vaccination, but will still need to be quarantined to make sure it is not infected. [Although the dog is current on its rabies vaccination, it is recommended by the rabies compendium to revaccinate immediately and then placed under a 45-day quarantine, instead of a 4-month quarantine. The compendium implies this quarantine may be a home quarantine provided certain qualifications are met. - Mod.TG]

Polk County had 5 confirmed cases of rabies in 2021, and 2 in 2020.

Officials warn residents if a wild mammal is acting aggressive or appears sick to stay away and contact Animal Control immediately.

[Byline: Matt Reeser]

